<span id="freeTextContainer9159492847859533052">This gentleman just gave a speech at my son&apos;s school. His story is so amazing. He cheated death so many times, and never knew why. He was called &quot;Lucky Louie!&quot;. Only after he returned, got married, and was dealing with stress by drinking did he become a Christian! His wife took him to hear Billy Graham, and has lived his life for Christ ever since! The book is not religious at all. It tells his incredible story, and only at the end describes his religious conversion. God saved his life so many t</span>
  <span id="freeText9159492847859533052" style="display:none">This gentleman just gave a speech at my son's school. His story is so amazing. He cheated death so many times, and never knew why. He was called "Lucky Louie!". Only after he returned, got married, and was dealing with stress by drinking did he become a Christian! His wife took him to hear Billy Graham, and has lived his life for Christ ever since! The book is not religious at all. It tells his incredible story, and only at the end describes his religious conversion. God saved his life so many times, so that some day he could touch the lives of others. </span>
